                "type": "dialogue",
                "text": "Let me show you how to see this. First, I count the containers. 1 bag, 2 bags, 3 bags. Then I look inside one bag: 5 items. Every bag has that same 5. So it's 3 groups of 5. The circles show it the same way: 3 circles, 5 dots in each. The graph shows it too: 3 symbols, each symbol stands for 5. Different containers, same structure. All three show 3 groups of 5.",
